{
  "stem": "13313.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Since we were-- since we were not observant, and-- and we lived in this particular neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father, as a matter of fact, didn't even speak French because he was not-- he-- he had never really had the occasion to be able to go to grade school, I believe, because of his background.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a result, we spoke Flemish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we spoke Flemish like native-- native people, so our-- you could not tell by our-- our accent that were not-- that we were Jewish, which, in a way, was one of the major reasons why we survived the war, which is paradoxical.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this is-- this is--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, only in school.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then since our neighborhood-- there were-- I don't recall having any Jewish children in our neighborhood, so most of the kids I played with were neighbors' kids, which were all Christian, mostly Catholic.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the main religion there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Only because we had an aunt and an uncle, my late father's brother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Plus we also had--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jacques.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and we also had a sister of my mother's.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Her name was Rosa.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I had an aunt and an uncle and their families.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I recall that only on the major holidays we-- we-- we met to celebrate those like we did.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's Passover, Rosh Hashanah, but that was about the--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mostly, it was in our home because there were-- we were a little bit better off than they were.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't make out as well as my-- as my parents did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Things began to change when, first of all there were the rumblings about what was going on in-- in Poland after the occupation of Poland, I think in September, 1939.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then there were rumblings about Hitler, the Jewish-- his attitude to the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
